ield emission\nfrom microscopic filaments, but it appears instead to be related to the quality\nof the wire surface in terms of corrosion and the nature of its oxide layer.\nThis study concludes that some surface treatments, in particular nitric acid\ncleaning for stainless steel wires, can bringing about at least\norder-of-magnitude improvements in overall electron emission rates, and this\nshould help the next generation of detectors achieve the required electrostatic\nperformance.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 22 Jan 2018 18:26:54 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 11 Jun 2018 10:26:20 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-08-29"}
